The numbers are placed on a hexagonal lattice in a clockwise spiral.  
For a number \(n\) let its axial coordinates be \((q,r)\).  
The “ring’’ (hex‑distance from the centre) is  

\[
k = \max\bigl(|q|,\;|r|,\;|{-q-r}|\bigr).
\]

For a given ring \(k\) the first number (the one at \((k,0)\)) is  

\[
a_k = 3k(k-1)+2 .
\]

Walking round the ring we use the six direction vectors  

\[
d_0=(-1,-1),\; d_1=(-1,0),\; d_2=(0,1),\; d_3=(1,1),\; d_4=(1,0),\; d_5=(0,-1)
\]

with each side taken for \(k\) steps.

---

### 1.  Find the coordinates of 2026  

The maximal number in ring \(k\) is  

\[
M_k = 3k(k+1)+1 .
\]

\(M_{25}=1951,\; M_{26}=2107\); therefore \(2026\) is in ring \(k=26\).

Its offset in the ring  

\[
\text{off}=2026-(M_{25}+1)=2026-1952=74 .
\]

The first \(26\) steps are on side 0, the next \(26\) on side 1, the remaining \(22\) on side 2, giving the coordinate  

\[
(26,0) \xrightarrow{\;d_0\;26\;}\;(0,-26)\xrightarrow{\;d_1\;26\;}\;(-26,-26)
\xrightarrow{\;d_2\;22\;}\;(-26,-4).
\]

Thus \(2026\) is at \((-26,-4)\).

---

### 2.  The six neighbours  

Adding the six direction vectors to \((-26,-4)\) gives  

\[
\begin{aligned}
&(-27,-5),\; (-27,-4),\; (-26,-3),\; (-25,-3),\; (-25,-4),\; (-26,-5).
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 3.  Convert each neighbour to its number  

For a neighbour we first find its ring \(k\) (the hex‑distance) and then its offset in that ring.

| coordinate | \(k\) | side | offset in the ring | number |
|------------|------|------|----------------|--------|
| \((-27,-5)\) | 32 | side 1 (west side) | \(k-q = 32-(-27)=59\) | \(a_{32}+59 = 2978+59 = 3037\) |
| \((-27,-4)\) | 31 | side 1 | \(31-(-27)=58\) | \(2792+58 = 2850\) |
| \((-26,-3)\) | 29 | side 1 | \(29-(-26)=55\) | \(2438+55 = 2493\) |
| \((-25,-3)\) | 28 | side 1 | \(28-(-25)=53\) | \(2270+53 = 2323\) |
| \((-25,-4)\) | 29 | side 1 | \(29-(-25)=54\) | \(2438+54 = 2492\) |
| \((-26,-5)\) | 31 | side 1 | \(31-(-26)=57\) | \(2792+57 = 2849\) |

(The “side 1’’ is the western side of the hexagon; on that side the offset from the start of the ring is \(k-q\).)

---

### 4.  Sum of the six neighbours  

\[
3037+2850+2493+2323+2492+2849 = 16\,044 .
\]

\[
\boxed{16044}
\]
